headline.print_headline: California Bill Seeks to Curb Sexually Explicit Internet Bullying by Teens
headline.main: California Bill Seeks to Curb Sexually Explicit Internet Bullying by Teens

lead_paragraph: Teenagers who share sexually explicit images of others on the Internet to harass them could soon face tougher punishment under California legislation proposed on Friday, spurred by the suicide of a teen after images of her sexual assault were circulated to other students.
